<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-161-157 </DOCNO><DOCID>10 768 239</DOCID><JOURNAL>Communications News  May 1991 v28 n5 p28(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Performance monitoring: the pro-active approach. (communicationsnetworks) (Test Equipment)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Carley, Don.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Organizations can enhance their communications networks by takinga pro-active approach toward performance monitoring.andP;  Performancemonitoring can help companies prevent network failures.andO;Non-intrusive monitoring forces signals through network elementsthat can be viewed as failure points.andP;  The types of payloadmonitoring that can be accomplished through non-intrusivemonitoring include full call progress reporting for circuits aftermultiplexing; protocol, Signaling System 7 message set, and ISDNmessage set confirmation; and bandwidth utilization.andP;  Theattributes that intelligent test platforms must have includeco-existing alarm reporting systems, autonomy, and flexibility.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Performance MeasurementMethodsNetwork ManagementHardware MaintenanceTestingCommunications ManagementNetwork Monitors.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>